******SCP********* 
#Copy a local file to a remote server:
scp /path/to/local/file.txt user@remote_host:/path/to/remote/directory/

#Copy a file from a remote server to the local machine: 
scp user@remote_host:/path/to/remote/file.txt /path/to/local/directory/

#Copy a directory recursively from local to remote:
scp -r /path/to/local/directory/ user@remote_host:/path/to/remote/

********Netcat********
On the receiving machine
    nc -l -p 12345 > received_document.txt
On the sending machine
    nc <receiver_IP> 12345 < document.txt
